My work day routine that I can’t miss. Aroma therapy that exudes calmness and hyper focus. 

Setting intentions for my work day and repeating affirmations like: “I am gifted with creative hands. I am talented. I am loving with people. I listen actively and reflect. I slay brows. I have great vibes. My team is amazing. I place my trust in the universe. I am protected. God loves me.”

Before every single procedure (if you’re a client of mine, I sometimes ask you to do this with me but most often I do this alone) I take two deep cleansing breathes to release any tension then I start tattooing.  If you’re able to have a diffuser, try aroma therapy. It really helps!

PMU Tip: (Save this post and Share) Shading in the front first allows the pigment to oxidize and settle into the skin. While that happens, you can then either shade your way towards the tail or begin at the tail to work your way into the head of the brows. 

🖊️It is easier to blend into the lightly shaded front head than it is to shade the entire tail and body have it look dark to then aim for a light ombré front. 

🖊️In PMU, it is best to be conservative. Because we can’t take away, but we can always add.

Is your work is fading too quickly?

When I first started out, some of us were  taught that PMU ink is supposed to get tattooed in the epidermis layer of the skin, which is why its called “semi-permanent”. With the amount of science and nursing classes I took during the first 3 years of college, this didn’t make complete sense to me if the epidermis layer regenerates every 28 days with the expectation that results should last anywhere between 6 months-3 years. 🤔

I took more trainings and asked more questions. I’ve learned that:

If you Tattoo too shallow (epidermis)= poor retention. Trauma to the skin. Can’t hear the needle to skin. Listen and feel for the difference in vibration of machine and skin. 

The right spot(dermis): PMU ink is supposed to get deposited in the Dermis layer right underneath the stratum basale (lowest layer of the epidermis). See perfect pixelation when you wipe and you see pinpoint bleeding when you microblade. Pinch or spread the stroke to see if the skin is still intact. 

Tattoo too deep (hypodermis): risk of pigment migration. YES ink can migrate. Ink blurs. Heals cool. Not clean or crisp. More bleeding. 

Everyone’s skin thickness is different. Even shown on the same cadaver, different parts of the body has different skin thickness. Hence why some tattoos on the body heal better than other parts and why hands and feet are probably the worst areas to tattoo. 

If you’re an artist, learning to go at the proper depth can be challenging. I suggest scratching a small area of the skin first to get a feel of thickness and adjust pressure from there. Age, Ethnicity, products and medication are contributing factors to skin thickness. 

TOO MANY FACTORS: Even if you tattoo at the proper depth, it’s also important to remember the clients lifestyle and how closely they follow proper aftercare. 

Like & Comment if you want me to explain in another posts factors that also contribute to premature fading.

Come to work with me. 

I set intentions for the work day even if it’s just brows all day. Getting my mind in the right space is important. 

Board of Health requires you to wash hands for a full 2-3 minutes before you start work. Did you know that?

I use dry cleaner bags or plastic wrap to cover the head of the bed. 
Aroma therapy is vital for my mental health. I am obsessed with Young Living essential oils.

Brow mapping area is separate from my work tray. One deals with open skin and the other does not so we dont cross contaminate. 

I try to have fresh flowers every week and I buy them myself. It’s a lovely gift. 
I only video-graphed the clients who signed waivers, the other two chose to stay private and thats OK! But it was a 4 brow client day. 

I tidy up here and there in between. We do it all and wear many hats as entrepreneurs. 

@browlady.sophina comes by often to say hi and ask questions when she’s not busy @browlady.Kim is in her zone slaying away. 

I love my “job”. If you knew you wouldn’t fail what would be your dream job? Comment below.

No I’m not about to karate chop anyone. 🤣 just getting ready for a procedure. So happy that I made an uncomfortable decision to pursue my visions. 

When you show up as your authentic self, you will attract the right people but you have to be okay with repelling them too. Accept that you’re not here to be liked by all. God made you as you are. The way you speak, how you say certain words, how you carry yourself, your personality, even the dark side of you. The events that has happened is meant to happen. It shapes you to be who you are this very day. Instead of feeling sorry for yourself, ask “what lessons am I supposed to learn from this?”. 

When you find your tribe even if it’s 50 people, show up for them! Don’t let the number of followers invalidate who you are or what you do. No one is you and that’s your superpower.

Hi friends! 👋🏻 Some of you might have seen in my stories that I was invited to be a guest speaker at the Boston Women’s Brunch held together by @EmpoweredWomenofBoston on March 26th, 2023. Thank you @thereelcassi for this opportunity! 😁

This is a level of discomfort that I have to break through, speaking to a live audience is not something that I am good at yet especially if I am going to be vulnerable and share a part of my story that I have not publicly spoken about. 

If you haven’t already done so, book your ticket so we can celebrate sisterhood through networking over brunch, there will be champagne and non-alcoholic beverages, and it also includes a headshot! If this is your first networking event, I know it can be intimidating, but remember you’re not the only one who’s nervous and the bigger picture is meeting like minded individuals who have a goal to elevate, inspire, and empower one another. AH-MAZING!

Gray brows can be a result of various factors. UV rays is the biggest reason for why pigment fades. Macrophages is another. Sweat pushes pigment out through osmosis. Glycolic acids regenerates skin cells twice as fast (2 weeks Vs 4 weeks). Tattooing too deep causes ink to appear cooler bc it’s deeper into the skin. Pmu is meant to fade and when it does, warm color gets lost. Often times, putting orange back in to neutralize blue or gray helps! Here’s an example of a color correction. Try using a color that does not contain carbon black color code: CI # 77266. 

Color theory is tough but understanding the color wheel is the first step. We talk about this in my course.

In celebration of Women’s History Month in March, I was invited to speak at the Empowered Women of Boston’s brunch event. It was certainly empowering to be able to inspire women while emphasizing the need for authenticity. 

I spoke about breaking generational trauma thats encoded in our DNA, how to choose ourselves through love, self awareness, and asking the audience: “When, where, and with whom do we have to sacrifice our authenticity to appease others?” Self love is a never ending journey. Harnessing the energy of love as a frequency leads to emotional mastery and ascends us to higher vibrations, which then leads to more opportunities that truly align with what we are meant to do, our true purpose. 

This was my first speech and it was scary but it felt right to my core. Sharing the “stage” with 4 other incredible women who all share the same purpose was an impactful experience that nourishes my soul. I’ve learned that this is something that I’d like to do more often. 

My favorite part was making connections with women who have a similar mindset. I also value the vulnerability and the safe space allowing us to share without judgement. I am so excited for the next event!

Q: What was the moment you knew you wanted to start your business?

A: When I was 19 years old after I got fired from Bugaboo Creek Steakhouse in South Portland, ME. I carefully folded my dirty maroon apron and placed it on the General Managers desk and walked out through the front door waving goodbye to the rest of the servers and hostess. I felt elated like a ton of weight lifted off my chest. Frankly, it was the most toxic environment I have ever worked in. Most of the staff seemed miserable. It makes sense as to why they shut down permanently a few years later. Some staff were very nice. Either way, I never felt like I belonged there. Like there was more for me. 

Getting fired forced me to consider entrepreneurship. What could be worse than being jobless? I didn’t start microblading back then but I did learn about what it entrepreneurship could look like for me. In the meantime, I got new bartending job at a Country Club which allowed me to speak to members who were successful. Surrounded by wealthy smart executives is what I needed. I picked their brains when they asked me personal questions. It was enough for me to see a world where I can actually make my own money on my own terms. It wasn’t easy but I am so glad that I realized my own potential even when others who thought they were better didn’t. I sat down wrote a business plan while bartending at the country club and finishing up at the School of Business in Southern Maine University. 

Happy to look back now and say that I earn AT LEAST 5x more than the General Manager of Bugaboo Creek based on Glassdoor. Not trying to boast. The point is no one will believe in you as much as you will. Entrepreneurship is scary but if it’s executed with the proper system and framework plus you are coachable then you WILL grow to succeed.

⚠️My story can be triggering.

The times I’ve chosen myself:
Refusing to live with a pedophile perpetrator at age 15 meant living away from home and finishing high school using someone else’s home address. 

Ending a physically abusive, manipulative, gaslighting relationship of 6.5 years meant being homeless for 3 months. 

Choosing to purge certain family members because they don’t understand boundaries and now as an adult I can protect that inner child in me who needed love and validation. This gives me power to protect my own children from the disgusting shit I grew up experiencing. 

Choosing to move to MA from ME to start all over has been such a blessing. I’ve lived through extremely uncomfortable situations BY CHOICE or consequences of my decisions. It felt lonely and depressed but having hope that if I continue to do ONE thing each week that serves the life I truly want I knew my dreams of having a safe, loving, and comfortable environment will soon exist. 

I may not be the wealthiest but I feel so rich with love! I may not respond to my friends immediately but I have chosen understanding friends who still love me for me. I may still be patched up with missing pieces but I love so hard and I am not the same person I was back then.  Choose yourself even when it’s going to be hard. Prioritize your mental and physical health. I promise it’ll be worth it!

Thankful for God’s provision through it all. 

P.s. let me know if you like to hear stories of personal growth in the comments. Most of us like to only share highlights of our lives but id like to be more authentic with my journey.

Let's talk about what happens when you drink coffee before your brow appointment ⬇️

☕️ Blood Flow: Coffee and other caffeinated beverages can increase blood flow and blood pressure, which may cause excess bleeding during the microblading process. This can make it more difficult for the pigment to be applied evenly and can also result in a less effective healing process.

☕️ Sensitivity: Caffeine can also make your skin more sensitive, which can increase discomfort during the tattoo process. It is important to remain as comfortable as possible during the procedure in order to achieve the best possible results.

☕️ Swelling: Caffeine is known to cause dehydration and can also contribute to swelling in the body. This can make it more difficult for the skin to heal properly after the microblading procedure, and can also lead to additional discomfort and irritation.

❓What is the best advice you have ever received?

The best advice was a change in my perspective. The fear of losing. The fear of failure. The fear of fucking up. The fear of looking stupid in front of family, friends, and those who secretly want us to fail. This fear hindered me from doing so many things that I’ve dreamt of. And sometimes when I think about new ventures, this fear this brain of mine tells me to stop and play it safe. I am certain that some of you can relate!

🌟 Start imperfect. Accept that you will MESS UP its called a learning curve or the beta phase for a reason. You don’t wake up as an expert that comes with trying it over and over and over again. Use what you already have. Confidence comes from overcoming many hurdles. Do NOT compare yourself to others, it’s detrimental. 

🌟 Be careful with whom you share your ideas with. Even if they mean well, even if they care about you, their input could stop you from being starting and becoming great. I used to seek validation or run ideas with people (and I still do) but ultimately I already know what I’m gonna do, which is doing me still. Keep friends who will help nurture you and your venture. Side story: I recall telling people about becoming a microblading artist and I heard crickets or “how are you going to make money doing that???” “Just stick to a trade..” LOL

I thank GOD every single day for putting the idea in MY head. When you have ideas and people don’t understand you, it’s because it’s not meant for them it’s meant for YOU!

Why it matters to me and how does it affect you as a client, potential client,  or prospective student? ⭐️ 

This 100hr course is required by the Board of Health in various towns in MA and ME to get your body art permit. It’s very detailed to ensure that our community stays safe. It’s curated so the students understand the CONCEPT, science and art behind every step so they can practice and implement properly and can fix their own mistakes. 

As a potential client, AAM artists are held to the highest standards. If we have high standards, so should you! We aim to provide a beautiful enhancement in a safe clean environment!

What is 𝙇𝙞𝙥 𝙉𝙚𝙪𝙩𝙧𝙖𝙡𝙞𝙯𝙖𝙩𝙞𝙤𝙣? 💋 

Lip neutralization involves using specialized pigments and techniques to neutralize any unwanted undertones or discoloration on the lips, creating a more even and uniform base for further lip enhancements or makeup application.

This treatment is commonly sought after by clients who have naturally darker or uneven lip pigmentation, such as hyperpigmentation, or scars. The process aims to correct and balance the lip color to achieve a more desired or natural-looking appearance.

Today we’re talking about aftercare and how you can care for your brows after you leave our studio! ⭐️

Step 1. Remove lymphatic fluid by dabbing your brows every 5 mins for one hour then every 15 mins for 6 hours. 

Step 2. Wash brows with a gentle cleanser.

step 3. Apply a TINY amount of healing ointment with a clean q-tip. If your skin is oily, use less. The brows should NOT look shiny. 

Additionally, please follow your artists recommendation. These instructions have yield great healed results and are recommended for our Brow Lady clients =) 

📌 If you’re an artist, feel free to use these instructions also!

NOTE: Witch hazel helps to alleviate itchiness typically around day 4 ish is when you might feel it.

More aftercare tips can be found on our website! (link in bio)

You might be thinking this is another “count your blessings” post, but this is the type of inner work that I do everyday that has altered my perspective, and I wanted to share it with you because it helps with manifesting as well as opening new doors for better opportunities in all aspects of life. 📖👇🏼

People are attracted to vibrant energy; shifting your energy from negative to attractive can be hard (if not impossible) at times, especially if you’re grieving or going through something traumatic.

💡 Here’s what I do when I am having a shitty day or a great day:

Practice gratitude. You can pick 5 things to be grateful for, but if you REALLYYYY want this to work then list 10 things and hyper focus on the 10 things you’re happy about. I’ll share two examples: 

1. Sometimes I dread going into work. But, I am glad my eyes are good enough for me to see up close, my hands are fully functioning, my mind is more than capable, and I have a JOB. I can provide and live a comfortable life. AMAZING!

2. Sometimes my husband gets on my nerves and my coping mechanism is to run away lol, INSTEAD I am thankful for a supportive partner who pushes me (sometimes a little too hard) to chase my dreams, he is careful and loving when he touches me because he understands my trauma, he is here and he is alive, he is present in our kids lives, and he tells me every day how much he loves me. I AM SO GRATEFUL AND LUCKY!

💛 Shift your mindset and list the wonderful things of every situation and you will feel happier, thus radiate positive frequencies, and more good things will come. I promise!

.
.
.

Why choose to get your brows tattooed (besides the obvious answer: that it’s a time saver!)? 👀👇

❤️ Conditions like alopecia or brow hair loss can result in the absence of brows. PMU offers a solution for those seeking to restore the look of natural brows and regain facial symmetry.

❤️ As we age, our eyebrows may become sparser or lose their shape. Brow tattooing can help combat the effects of aging, creating a more youthful and well-defined brow shape.

❤️ Some individuals may have allergies or sensitivities to traditional brow makeup products. Brow tattooing can provide a hypoallergenic alternative, allowing them to enjoy the enhanced appearance of eyebrows without any adverse reactions.

❓Not sure if you’re due for a touch-up? Send us a photo of your brows and we’ll let you know what we think!

While everyone’s timelines will be a little different when it comes to needing a color refresh, here are a few reasons why it’s important to book these appointments ⬇️

✨ Over time, factors like sun exposure, natural skin exfoliation, and the body’s metabolic processes can cause the tattooed pigment to gradually fade. A touch-up session will help to refresh and refine the color, ensuring that your brows remain vibrant.

✨ Our facial features evolve subtly as we age, and so do our brows. Annual touch-ups offer an opportunity to reassess the shape and structure of your brows, ensuring they continue to flatter your face in the most flattering and up-to-date manner. 

✨ Just like any work of art, proper maintenance is key to preservation. An annual touch-up will allow us to monitor and address any potential issues, such as uneven fading or loss of pigment.

Common FAQs 𝘼𝙉𝙎𝙒𝙀𝙍𝙀𝘿: "Will the powder brows look natural, or will they appear too dark and harsh?" ⬇️

A: Powder brows are designed to create a soft and natural-looking effect. The goal of powder brows is to mimic the appearance of softly shaded, filled-in eyebrows, similar to the look achieved with eyebrow powder or pencil. 

𝙎𝙒𝙄𝙋𝙀 to see the comparison of our client's natural everyday brow makeup to her fresh new powder brows! 👀 The goal was to create a set of brows she's used to and comfortable with, just with a splash of our expertise.

🖤 The powder brow technique allows for a buildable effect, meaning the intensity of the color can be adjusted based on the client's preferences. 

💡 Remember, the color may appear slightly more vibrant immediately after the appointment, but it will gradually soften about 30-40% as the skin heals.

Should you be skipping your touch-ups? 👀 NOPE! Swipe to read why ⬅️

After your initial brow appointment, we technically don't consider your brows to be fully complete or the job to be done until the second visit. This is because as the brows undergo the healing process, it's normal that your brows may lighten/fade more in some areas than others. So the 'perfection' visit (also known as the touch-up) allows us to do just that; perfect our work!

How can the 𝒓𝒊𝒈𝒉𝒕 set of brows make a difference for your face? ⬇️

✨ Eyebrows act as a natural frame for your eyes and face.

✨ Eyebrows are essential for conveying emotions and expressions. The way you shape and style your eyebrows can affect how approachable, serious, or friendly you appear.

✨ The right brow shape can help balance out your facial features by creating symmetry/harmony and complimenting the shape of your face and eyes.

✨ As we age, eyebrows tend to thin out and lose their shape. A more flattering and full set of brows can help rejuvenate your look.

✔️ To make the most of your eyebrows and their impact on your face, we always consider factors like face shape, eye shape, skin type, and your personal preferences when it comes to the mapping portion of your appointment.

Fill in the blank: I feel most confident when _________________ ⬇️

Confidence isn't something that magically appears overnight; it's a skill that can be developed and honed over time. But I've learned that it's an important skill to have both in life, and in your business! 

Some things that help me with both building and maintaining my confidence:

💛 Replacing self-doubt with positive affirmations. Challenging negative thoughts and replacing them with constructive ones.

💛  Break up goals into small and achievable tasks. Each success and milestone reached should be celebrated, and that can help to boost confidence.

💛 The more you know, the more confident you'll feel. Invest in continuous learning and take the time to really prepare for things like meetings, presentations, or projects.

Come behind the scenes with me as I do some lesson recording! 🎥 What are some tips you guys have for filming/creating your content? My top 3 would be:

▶️ Plan your content! Outline the purpose and/or message of what you’re trying to create before pressing record. I also find creating a script or a rough plan helps ensure a more successful result.

▶️ Lighting matters. Natural light is usually the best, but if filming indoors, use soft, diffused lighting to avoid harsh shadows. Also consider investing in affordable lighting equipment, such as ring lights or softboxes.

▶️ Fake your confidence until you make it! Don’t forget to maintain eye contact with the camera to stay connected with your viewers. Speak clearly and you can also try using a teleprompter for scripted content.

10 Easy Self Care Activities You Can Do TODAY (number 10 is my fav 😉)! ↴

➡️ Take a walk in nature or around your neighborhood to get some fresh air and exercise.
➡️ Escape into a good book for a while, whether it's fiction, non-fiction, or a self-help book.
➡️ Create a calming playlist or listen to your favorite music to boost your mood.
➡️ Reflect on your thoughts and feelings by writing in a journal. It can be a great way to release pent-up emotions.
➡️ Stretch your body with some yoga or simple stretching exercises to release tension.
➡️ Prepare a nutritious meal or snack for yourself. Cooking can be a therapeutic activity.
➡️ Write down things you are grateful for in your life.
➡️ Tackle a small area of your living space and declutter it. A tidy environment can have a positive impact on your mental state.
➡️ Take a break from screens and social media to reduce digital overwhelm.
➡️ Give yourself a spa day with a face mask, manicure/pedi, or finally book that brow appointment 😆

💬 Let me know which #selfcare activity you plan to do for yourself today in the comments!

Outlines don’t have to be bold and solid. It just has to be visible enough for your eyes to tattoo within the lines. If your style is to have a softer outline, try doing pointillism (dots) and build slowly until you’ve reached the desired saturation. 

I like using a 1RL (round liner) 0.35mm (diameter of each needle) bc the diameter is thicker and works on most skin types. 

Let me know if you use pointillism with your art work in the comments below! ⬇️⬇️

❗Microblading/PMU brows isn’t ZERO maintenance, it’s low maintenance. 

Maintaining your brows mean:
→ Grooming 
→ Tinting

After few failed hair transplant sessions, this client decided to book an SMP session with us! 

🌿 What is SMP?
Scalp Micropigmentation, or SMP, is a cutting-edge, non-invasive treatment that replicates the appearance of a closely-shaved head or a fuller head of hair. This technique involves the skillful application of microdots of pigment to your scalp, mimicking the natural look of hair follicles. The result? A remarkably realistic and natural hairline that’s almost indistinguishable from the real thing.

For years I have been yearning for a type of healing that books, therapy, relationships with others could not provide. I knew I had to dig deep within myself but needed some guidance. During a brow session, I heard about Sedona from more than a handful of you who have shared your stories about the healing energy there. So, I flew my family including the in-laws to Sedona and it is by far our favorite place. The shift in energy felt like my soul was being cradled. It wasn’t just a vacation that I needed, I have been taking quite a bit of those this year but this one in Arizona did something different to me and I felt more clarity, more at peace. I felt closer to home. Before I sound crazier, I will just say that visiting Sedona at least once is worth the trip even for sightseeing and hiking. The vast sky and the red rocks will reset your mind. I can’t wait to visit again. ✈️ 

Have you ever visited Sedona, AZ? Did you feel anything?? What other places have the healing effect? I would love to hear about your experiences! ⬇️

Outlines can be hard! 🥴 I like to start at the bottom arch and work my way towards me counting “1-2-3 and move on” to the next section. The counting means I am overlapping 3x in the same line.

The top frame I count only to 2 bc I want that to be super light.

Outlines don’t need to be dark. If they’re dark then you need more ink to blend. But again, that all depends on your style! When it comes to art, your hands eyes and vision looks different to someone else. That’s the beauty of this work.

Today we’re talking about aftercare and how you can care for your brows after you leave our studio! ⭐️

Step 1. Remove lymphatic fluid by dabbing your brows every 5 mins for one hour then every 15 mins for 6 hours.

Step 2. Wash brows with a gentle cleanser.

step 3. Apply a TINY amount of healing ointment with a clean q-tip. If your skin is oily, use less. The brows should NOT look shiny.

Additionally, please follow your artists recommendation. These instructions have yield great healed results and are recommended for our Brow Lady clients =)

📌 If you’re an artist, feel free to use these instructions also!

NOTE: Witch hazel helps to alleviate itchiness typically around day 4 ish is when you might feel it.

More aftercare tips can be found on our website! (link in bio)

A day in the studio. Being transparent about pricing (it’s also listed on our website) and number of Microblading appointments. Don’t add the numbers up as profit because there’s overhead etc to run a business. 

After doing brows for 5 years, I am doing a TON of touch ups. I love seeing how I’ve progressed from a year-3 years. Because of the organic pigment lines I’ve used in the past, the brows have healed ashy. Other factors can be because of UV rays and macrophages in our body eating away at pigment molecules. My pressure has always been light so I know I’m not implanting ink too deep in the dermis layer. Which is why I’ve switched to inorganic or hybrids and have been color correcting with more orange that does not contain carbon black. After reading the ingredients and color index, I was shocked that some artists who collaborated with popular pigment lines use black in a modifying color. Adding a color containing carbon black to ashy brows only makes the brows even more gray. Crazy. 

If you’re an artist, learn to color correct! Always be conservative in color and saturation and dilute your pigments! 

Let’s keep our clients happy in the long run and save our industry by using pigments that are meant to fade. Otherwise, we would only pack in more ink making brows look very tattooish. I’m guilty of it but now I feel confident in saying no to requests and sticking to it. You’ll be happy that you did.

Before & after combo brows 🧚 She left with her brows, but better! The powder shading and added hairstrokes at the front of her brows help to add more definition to her overall appearance. Swipe for another look ⬅️

Her brows will heal 30-40% lighter, leaving her with full, soft, and natural-looking brows.

Brows may heal lighter initially than you may expect, which is better than too dark! But this is why the touch-up session is crucial for fine-tuning and perfecting our work.

7 tips for keeping your tattooed brows 𝒐𝒏 𝒇𝒍𝒆𝒆𝒌 for as long as possible:

📌 Aftercare is the most important factor for optimal retention
📌 Avoid tanning beds or sun tanning
📌 Avoid active skincare ingredients on and around the treated area
📌 Avoid soaking the brows in sea/salt water
📌 Avoid excessive sweating & wipe sweat off the brows
📌 Avoid using thick and heavy makeup on the eyebrows, including foundation
📌 Avoid DIY face masks, retinol, and exfoliants
